---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="boyoung — info" currentPath="/info">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 pb-24 pt-2 md:px-10 md:pt-4">
		<div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12 md:gap-10 lg:gap-14">
			<div class="md:col-span-7 lg:col-span-8">
				<section class="mb-12 md:mb-16">
					<h1
						class="mb-4 font-serif text-xl font-medium normal-case tracking-normal text-ink md:text-2xl"
					>
						Description of myself as an artist.
					</h1>
					<div
						class="font-serif text-[0.98rem] leading-[1.65] text-ink/90 md:text-[1.02rem]"
					>
						<p>
							I work slowly, with graphite and color on paper, letting forms emerge from
							repeated marks and small accidents. My practice sits between observation and
							invention: lilies, hands, and domestic light return often, less as symbols than as
							temperatures and weights on the page. I am interested in surfaces that feel almost
							fragile—where the image could dissolve if you looked away—and in the small drama of
							edges, smudges, and halftones that refuse to behave.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-4">
							Recent bodies of work gather botanical studies alongside fragments of text and
							pattern, treating the sheet as a room you can walk around in. Exhibitions and
							editions are kept intentionally intimate; the shop holds prints and objects that
							extend these drawings into daily life. This site is a quiet index of those pieces,
							offered without hurry.
						</p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2
						class="mb-4 font-serif text-xl font-medium normal-case tracking-normal text-ink md:text-2xl"
					>
						Description of myself as an artist in korean
					</h2>
					<div
						class="font-serif text-[0.98rem] leading-[1.75] text-ink/90 md:text-[1.02rem] [&_p+p]:mt-4"
					>
						<p>
							저는 종이 위에서 연필과 색을 천천히 겹쳐가며 형태를 드러내는 작업을 합니다. 관찰과
							상상 사이에서 백합, 손, 집 안의 빛 같은 소재가 반복되는데, 이들은 상징이라기보다
							온도와 무게처럼 느껴지길 바랍니다. 시선을 돌리면 이미지가 스르르 사라질 듯한 표면,
							번지는 선과 얼룩의 작은 극적 순간에 관심이 있습니다.
						</p>
						<p>
							최근 작업은 식물 스케치와 짧은 글귀, 무늬의 단편을 한 장의 방처럼 배치하는 방식에
							가깝습니다. 전시와 에디션은 소규모로 유지하고, 샵에서는 일상으로 닿는 판화와 오브제를
							소개합니다. 이 웹사이트는 그 기록을 천천히 엮어 둔 색인입니다.
						</p>
					</div>
				</section>
			</div>

			<aside class="flex flex-col gap-10 md:col-span-5 lg:col-span-4">
				<div>
					<h2 class="sr-only">contact</h2>
					<ul
						class="space-y-3 font-sans text-sm font-medium lowercase tracking-[var(--tracking-sans)] text-ink"
					>
						<li>
							<a href="mailto:hello@example.com" class="text-ink no-underline hover:opacity-70">
								hello@example.com
							</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://www.instagram.com/"
								class="text-ink no-underline hover:opacity-70"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
							>
								instagram
							</a>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-auto">
					<div
						class="aspect-square max-w-sm overflow-hidden rounded-sm border border-black/5 bg-white shadow-sm"
					>
						<img
							src="/info-feature.svg"
							alt=""
							class="h-full w-full object-cover"
							width="400"
							height="400"
							loading="lazy"
						/>
					</div>
				</div>
			</aside>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
